                <p class="hero-subtitle">Learn how to use the MC AFK Tracker effectively</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Help Content -->
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-12">
            <div class="card">
                <div class="card-header">
                    <h2>📖 How to Use the MC AFK Tracker</h2>
                </div>
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h3>🎯 Overview</h3>
                    <p>The MC AFK Tracker helps you plan your Minecraft AFK farming sessions. Select your farm type, set your target items, and let the tracker calculate the optimal AFK time and provide real-time progress monitoring.</p>
                    
                    <h3>🔧 Step-by-Step Instructions</h3>
                    
                    <div class="step">
                        <h4>Step 1: Select Your Farm Type</h4>
                        <p>Choose from the dropdown menu which type of farm you're using. Each farm type has pre-configured production rates based on typical Minecraft farm designs:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>🔩 Iron Farm:</strong> 120 items per 5 minutes (Iron Ingots)</li>
                            <li><strong>🥇 Gold Farm:</strong> 80 items per 5 minutes (Gold Ingots/Nuggets)</li>
                            <li><strong>🌾 Crop Farm:</strong> 200 items per 5 minutes (Wheat, Carrots, Potatoes)</li>
                            <li><strong>👾 Mob Farm:</strong> 150 items per 5 minutes (General mob drops)</li>
                            <li><strong>💀 Skeleton Farm:</strong> 180 items per 5 minutes (Bones, Arrows)</li>
                            <li><strong>🕷️ Spider Farm:</strong> 160 items per 5 minutes (String, Spider Eyes)</li>
                            <li><strong>🧟 Zombie Farm:</strong> 140 items per 5 minutes (Rotten Flesh, Iron)</li>
                            <li><strong>💥 Creeper Farm:</strong> 90 items per 5 minutes (Gunpowder)</li>
                            <li><strong>🐄 Cow Farm:</strong> 100 items per 5 minutes (Leather, Raw Beef)</li>
                            <li><strong>🐷 Pig Farm:</strong> 95 items per 5 minutes (Porkchops)</li>
                            <li><strong>🐔 Chicken Farm:</strong> 110 items per 5 minutes (Feathers, Raw Chicken)</li>
                            <li><strong>🐑 Sheep Farm:</strong> 85 items per 5 minutes (Wool, Mutton)</li>
                            <li><strong>🦆 Cod Farm:</strong> 130 items per 5 minutes (Cod)</li>
                            <li><strong>🐟 Salmon Farm:</strong> 125 items per 5 minutes (Salmon)</li>
                            <li><strong>🐠 Tropical Fish Farm:</strong> 75 items per 5 minutes (Tropical Fish)</li>
                            <li><strong>🐡 Pufferfish Farm:</strong> 70 items per 5 minutes (Pufferfish)</li>
                            <li><strong>🌱 Kelp Farm:</strong> 250 items per 5 minutes (Kelp)</li>
                            <li><strong>🍄 Mushroom Farm:</strong> 180 items per 5 minutes (Mushrooms)</li>
                            <li><strong>🎋 Bamboo Farm:</strong> 300 items per 5 minutes (Bamboo)</li>
                            <li><strong>🌵 Cactus Farm:</strong> 150 items per 5 minutes (Cactus)</li>
                            <li><strong>🍯 Honey Farm:</strong> 45 items per 5 minutes (Honey Bottles)</li>
                            <li><strong>🕯️ Wax Farm:</strong> 40 items per 5 minutes (Honeycomb)</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step">
                        <h4>Step 2: Set Your Target</h4>
                        <p>Enter the number of items you want to collect. This can be anything from a few stacks to several double chests worth of items.</p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step">
                        <h4>Step 3: Start the Timer</h4>
                        <p>Click the "Start AFK Timer" button to begin tracking your session. The timer will:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Show your progress in real-time</li>
                            <li>Display estimated completion time</li>
                            <li>Provide visual progress indicators</li>
                            <li>Calculate efficiency metrics</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step">
                        <h4>Step 4: Monitor Progress</h4>
                        <p>Watch the timer and progress bar to track your farming session. The analysis panel shows:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Total Time Required:</strong> How long you need to AFK</li>
                            <li><strong>Items per Hour:</strong> Production rate for your farm</li>
                            <li><strong>Progress Percentage:</strong> How much of your goal you've completed</li>
                            <li><strong>Estimated Completion:</strong> When your session will finish</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Tips Section -->
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-12">
            <div class="card">
                <div class="card-header">
                    <h2>💡 Pro Tips</h2>
                </div>
                <div class="card-body">
                    <div class="tip">
                        <h4>🎮 AFK Best Practices</h4>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Make sure your character is in the correct position for your farm</li>
                            <li>Check that all farm mechanisms are working before starting</li>
                            <li>Ensure your inventory has enough space for the items</li>
                            <li>Consider using an auto-clicker if your farm requires interaction</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>

                    <div class="tip">
                        <h4>⚡ Optimizing Farm Efficiency</h4>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Iron farms work best when you're the only player online</li>
                            <li>Mob farms may need periodic clearing of nearby caves</li>
                            <li>Crop farms benefit from proper lighting and water placement</li>
                            <li>Gold farms require being in the Nether with proper portal alignment</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>

                    <div class="tip">
                        <h4>🔧 Troubleshooting</h4>
                        <ul>
                            <li>If production seems low, check for mob cap issues</li>
                            <li>Ensure chunk loading for your farm area</li>
                            <li>Verify redstone contraptions are functioning properly</li>
                            <li>Check that hoppers and storage systems aren't full</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- About Section -->
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-12">
            <div class="card">
                <div class="card-header">
                    <h2>ℹ️ About MC AFK Tracker</h2>
                </div>
                <div class="card-body">
                    <p>MC AFK Tracker is designed to help Minecraft players optimize their AFK farming sessions. Whether you're gathering resources for a massive build project or just want to automate your resource collection, this tool provides the calculations and timing you need.</p>
                    
                    <p>The production rates are based on commonly used farm designs from the Minecraft community. Your actual rates may vary depending on your specific farm design, server performance, and game version.</p>
                    

                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

